tion": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/ohio/", "2/united states/ohio/adams/", "3/united states/ohio/adams/west union/"], "contributor": ["ohio history connection, columbus, oh"], "date": "1930-01-09", "dates": ["1930-01-09"], "description": ["OHIO UNIVERSITY POULTRY EXPERT Was the Principal Speaker At Banquet Given At Peebles Peebles OhioThanks to the gen erosity of Mr and Mrs B R Wright oole owners of the Wright Hatchery at Peebles upwards of seventyfive persons enjoyed a sumptous chicken dinner in the high school gymnasium here Thursday evening The occa sion was a gettogether meeting of pure blooded flock owners They were the guests of Mr and Mrs Wright together with a few special friends from Portsmouthadepts when it comes to sampling roasted fried stewed or baked chicken For quite a few years Mr and Mrs Wright have been conducting one of the best known hatcheries in the country From a very meager plant at the start the hatchery now boasts of twin incubators of 90000 egg ca pacity Chickens thus hatched have been sent to every conceivable part of the country But Mr and Mrs Wright are not satisfied with simply hatching chicksthey want to im prove the flocks of those who furnish them with eggs and they have spared no expense in bringing the flocks in and around Peebles up to the high est possible standard Only recently they visited some of the finest poul"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-07-02T21:16:08.084Z", "group": ["ndnp/ohi", "ohio-historical-society-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn83035189/1930-01-09/ed-1/?sp=3", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ohi:batch_ohi_fleur_ver01:data:sn83035189:00516993741:1930010901:0014/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=454&w=342", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ohi:batch_ohi_fleur_ver01:data:sn83035189:00516993741:1930010901:0014/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=909&w=685", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordi